  "description": "A vector is an element of a vector space — anything that can be added to others of its kind and scaled by numbers from a field. The word brings to mind arrows in space: a direction and a magnitude, drawn as a line segment with a pointed tip. That image is useful but narrow. Arrows in two- or three-dimensional space are vectors, but so are columns of numbers, polynomials, continuous functions, and sequences of real numbers. What makes something a vector is not what it looks like, but what you can do with it.\n",
